critique:
This executive order amends a previous order regarding what items are allowable as household goods and personal effects for government employees. It specifically addresses the inclusion of groceries, provisions, wines, liquors, animals, birds, or automobiles. The amendment allows for the inclusion of groceries and provisions during government rationing of foods. This appears to be a wartime measure during World War II. Considering the axes:
